# Future AGI Documentation Guidelines

## Before Publishing [IMPORTANT]
- Before removing or updating any URL, add redirects on the old URL to the new one
- Check for broken links present anywhere by running `mint broken-links` command

## File Structure Conventions
- All screenshots or media files must be inside `/screenshot/<complete-relative-path-of-the-respective-page>`
- Each page must have 'title' and 'description' tags for better SEO

## Naming Conventions
- Page names should be comprehensive and convey what the page is about without looking at the complete path
- For pages like "overview", use a more descriptive name like "overview - observe" to provide context

## Code Formatting
- If code snippets are available for multiple languages, use `code-groups` (https://www.mintlify.com/docs/components/code-groups#code-groups)

## Documentation Clarity
- Use tooltip tags (https://www.mintlify.com/docs/components/tooltips#tooltips) for complicated terminology
- End tooltips with "learn more" redirects to respective detailed pages
- Example:
  ```
  This will appear as a new <Tooltip tip="Dynamic columns are generated on-the-fly and contain data derived from other columns or external operations." cta="Learn more about dynamic columns" href="/future-agi/get-started/dataset/concept/dynamic-column">dynamic column</Tooltip> in your dataset.
  ```

## Product Documentation Structure
- Each product must contain:
  1. `overview` - top-level introduction with cross-functionality links
  2. `quickstart` - most common use-cases to get started
  3. `/how-to` - all possible use-cases structured as:
     - Setup instructions first
     - Most common isolated use-cases
     - Cross-functionality use-cases

## API Key References
- Use this callout whenever API key requirements are mentioned:
  ```
  <Callout icon="key" color="#FFC107" iconType="regular">Click [here](https://app.futureagi.com/dashboard/keys) to access API Key and Secret Key.</Callout>
  ```
